    • visitDataDependence

      public void visitDataDependence​(InstanceType from, InstanceType to, Collection<? extends Variable> fromVars, Variable toVar, DataDependenceType type) throws InterruptedException
      Description copied from interface: DependencesVisitor
      Gets called if a (dynamic) data dependence has been determined.
      Specified by:
      visitDataDependence in interface DependencesVisitor<InstanceType>
      Parameters:
      from - the instruction that depends on another
      to - the "target" of the data dependence
      fromVars - the set of variables used to produce the value of toVar (possibly empty, e.g. for LDC or ICONST). WARNING: this parameter is only set for read after write dependencies, not for write after read dependencies (there it is null)!!
      toVar - the variable through which the dependence exists (was written by to and read by from)
      type - the type of the data dependence (read after write / write after read)
      Throws:
      InterruptedException

    • visitPendingDataDependence

      public void visitPendingDataDependence​(InstanceType from, Variable var, DataDependenceType type) throws InterruptedException
      Description copied from interface: DependencesVisitor
      Gets called if there might be a data dependence that gets visited later. If the type is DataDependenceType.READ_AFTER_WRITE, then most probably DependencesVisitor.visitDataDependence(Object, Object, Collection, Variable, DataDependenceType) gets called exactly one (may also be that it is not called in some cases), but definitively, at some later point DependencesVisitor.discardPendingDataDependence(Object, Variable, DataDependenceType) is called. If the type is DataDependenceType.WRITE_AFTER_READ, then DependencesVisitor.visitDataDependence(Object, Object, Collection, Variable, DataDependenceType) may get called one or several times, and finally DependencesVisitor.discardPendingDataDependence(Object, Variable, DataDependenceType) is called.
      Specified by:
      visitPendingDataDependence in interface DependencesVisitor<InstanceType>
      Parameters:
      from - the instruction that depends on another
      var - the variable through which the dependence exists
      type - the type of the data dependence (read after write / write after read)
      Throws:
      InterruptedException

    • visitUntracedMethodCall

      public void visitUntracedMethodCall​(InstanceType instrInstance) throws InterruptedException
      Description copied from interface: DependencesVisitor
      Gets called each time a method call is encountered, but the called method was not traced. This is most often the case for native methods, but there are also methods in the java api that are excluded from tracing.
      Specified by:
      visitUntracedMethodCall in interface DependencesVisitor<InstanceType>
      Parameters:
      instrInstance - the instruction instance of the method call (the unterlying instruction is a MethodInvocationInstruction)
      Throws:
      InterruptedException
